Graceful-degrade when boxmot is installed but its tracker API is incompatible.

Upstream _create_boxmot_tracker() falls back from `boxmot.trackers` (>=11 API)
to the top-level `boxmot.*` classes on ImportError, but a boxmot MAJOR bump
(e.g. 22.x) removes those top-level classes, so the fallback raises
AttributeError -- uncaught by `except ImportError` -- and, with no ReID, the
outer handler re-raises: a hard crash on the first tracked frame. This makes
ANY boxmot instantiation failure degrade to the built-in _SimpleIoUTracker
(as the "boxmot not installed" path already does) instead of crashing.

Defence-in-depth on top of the boxmot==19.0.0 pin: the pin keeps the tested
API, this keeps the app alive if a future resolve drifts. Retire when the
equivalent fix lands upstream. Worth proposing to AutoPTZ/autoptz.

diff --git a/autoptz/engine/pipeline/track.py b/autoptz/engine/pipeline/track.py
index 0301643..85f8427 100644
--- a/autoptz/engine/pipeline/track.py
+++ b/autoptz/engine/pipeline/track.py
@@ -103,6 +103,23 @@ def _log_fallback_tracker_once() -> None:
     )
 
 
+# One-time guard for the "boxmot present but API incompatible" degrade path.
+_LOGGED_INCOMPATIBLE_BOXMOT = False
+
+
+def _log_incompatible_boxmot_once() -> None:
+    global _LOGGED_INCOMPATIBLE_BOXMOT
+    if _LOGGED_INCOMPATIBLE_BOXMOT:
+        return
+    _LOGGED_INCOMPATIBLE_BOXMOT = True
+    log.warning(
+        "boxmot is installed but its tracker API is incompatible (a major "
+        "release likely moved or renamed the tracker classes) — falling back to "
+        "the built-in lightweight IoU tracker. Pin a compatible boxmot to "
+        "restore occlusion-robust BoT-SORT + ReID.",
+    )
+
+
 # ── Lightweight fallback tracker (no boxmot) ────────────────────────────────────
 
 
@@ -351,13 +368,23 @@ def _create_boxmot_tracker(
     try:
         tracker = _instantiate(want_reid)
     except Exception:  # noqa: BLE001
